On Thu, Feb 6, 2020 at 7:58 AM Gerwen, J. van (Job) <Job.vanGerwen@student.ru.nl> wrote:
Dear Henk and Helmer,

This past Wednesday our project for GiPHouse has had his launch. In the project start, we, the managers, met up with our engineers. During this meeting we discussed the project proposal that you provided to us through GiPHouse. From this discussion a multitude of questions arose. For this reason we are wondering if there is a chance for us to meet next Wednesday 12th of February between 12.30 and 16.30 (the meeting could last shorter and can be shifted to a later moment that day, but that would be our preferred time slot for now). In this meeting we would like to introduce ourself and get to know you better to get a better understanding of the direction we are taking with this project. Additionally we can discuss preferred communication channels and frequency from your point of view.

Preferably this meeting would be done in person with our entire team. Future meetings can be done with just the management team and digitally if that is preferred or more convenient for either of the parties, but as a starting point we felt our engineers would benefit from getting to know you and the idea behind the project as well. We will prepare the meeting with some questions about the project description and some more general questions about the coming semester.

I would love to hear what your availability is for next week. If you cannot find a possibility to meet next Wednesday the 12th, I would prefer it you send us some proposed time slots that would suite you. 

We are very motivated and looking forward to working with you in realising a well drafted and crafted solution to your FA needs.

Yours,

The management team of CLST

